</div><div class="info-panel__citations info-panel__item"><a href="#tab-citations" class="btn btn--inverse btn--slim" data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="View Citations" aria-label="View Citations"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-format_quote"></i></a></div><div class="info-panel__formats info-panel__item"><a href="#core-collateral-purchase-access" class="btn btn--access" data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="Go to purchase options" aria-label="Go to purchase options"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-lock-open"></i><span class="link-text">Get Access</span></a></div></div></div></div></header><div data-core-nav="header" data-extent="frontmatter"><div class="core-nav-wrapper core-container" aria-label="Article navigation"><div><button aria-controls="article_sections_menu" aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Toggle section navigation menu"><i class="icon-list" aria-hidden="true"></i><span>Contents</span></button><nav id="article_sections_menu" aria-label="Contents" data-core-nav="article"><ul><li><a href="#core-sec-figures">Figures</a></li><li><a href="#bibliography">Suggested Readings</a></li></ul></nav></div><nav id="article_collateral_menu"><ul class="collateral-pill" data-core-nav="collateral"><li><a href="#core-collateral-info" aria-controls="core-collateral-info" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Information & Authors" title="Information & Authors" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-info"></i><span class="sr-only">Information & Authors</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-metrics" aria-controls="core-collateral-metrics" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Metrics & Citations" title="Metrics & Citations" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-metrics"></i><span class="sr-only">Metrics & Citations</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-purchase-access" aria-controls="core-collateral-purchase-access" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Get Access" title="Get Access" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-lock-open"></i><span class="sr-only">Get Access</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-references" aria-controls="core-collateral-references" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="References" title="References" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-references"></i><span class="sr-only">References</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-figures" aria-controls="core-collateral-figures" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Figures" title="Figures" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-photo"></i><span class="sr-only">Figures</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-tables" aria-controls="core-collateral-tables" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Tables" title="Tables" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-table"></i><span class="sr-only">Tables</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-media" aria-controls="core-collateral-media" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Media" title="Media" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-play-circle-filled"></i><span class="sr-only">Media</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-share" aria-controls="core-collateral-share" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Share" title="Share" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-share"></i><span class="sr-only">Share</span></a></li></ul></nav></div></div><div data-core-wrapper="content"><div id="abstracts" data-extent="frontmatter"><div class="core-container"><div class="core-first-page-image"><img alt="First page of PDF" src="/cms/10.1148/rg.250117/asset/rg.250117.fp.png_v03" loading="lazy" /></div></div></div><section id="bodymatter" data-extent="bodymatter" property="articleBody" typeof="Text"><div class="core-container"><section aria-labelledby="denial-block-title" class="denial-block "><h2 id="denial-block-title" class="denial-block__title">Get full access to this article</h2><p class="denial-block__text">View all available purchase options and get full access to this article.</p><div class="denial-block__cta"><a href="#core-collateral-purchase-access" class="btn btn--access"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-lock-open"></i><span>Get Access</span></a></div><footer class="denial-block__footer"><span>Already a Subscriber? </span><span>Sign in as an </span><a href="/action/showLogin?redirectUri=/doi/10.1148/rg.250117">individual</a><span> or via your </span><a href="/action/ssostart?uri=/doi/10.1148/rg.250117">institution</a></footer></section></div></section><section id="backmatter" data-extent="backmatter"><div class="core-container"><section id="core-sec-figures" data-type="figures"><h2>Figures</h2><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig1" class="graphic" aria-label="Color Doppler ultrasound shows a moderate-sized hematoma at the right breast biopsy site, managed conservatively without further intervention."><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.250117/asset/images/rg.250117.fig1.jpg" height="764" width="1600" aria-labelledby="fig1" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 1</span>. Postbiopsy findings in a 75-year-old woman undergoing antithrombotic therapy (clopidogrel) who presented to the emergency department 12 hours after US-guided CNB of the right breast (Breast Imaging and Reporting Data System [BI-RADS] category 4B). Color Doppler US image of the right breast biopsy site shows a moderate-sized fluid collection consistent with a hematoma with no active bleeding. This finding was managed with manual compression and pressure bandaging. No additional interventions were necessary.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.250117&amp;id=fig1">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig2" class="graphic" aria-label="Color Doppler ultrasound reveals a pseudoaneurysm at the right breast biopsy site, later confirmed by CT angiography and treated with thrombin injection."><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.250117/asset/images/rg.250117.fig2.jpg" height="835" width="1075" aria-labelledby="fig2" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 2</span>. Clinically significant postbiopsy bleeding in a 48-year-old otherwise healthy woman who underwent stereotactic biopsy for grouped coarse heterogeneous calcifications at the 10-o’clock position in the right breast (Breast Imaging and Reporting Data System [BI-RADS] category 4B). Despite surgical evacuation of an expanding hematoma at the biopsy site, the patient continued to experience bleeding. Further evaluation with CT angiography identified a 10-mm pseudoaneurysm of the prepectoral branch of the thoracoacromial artery. Color Doppler US image of the biopsy site shows the bidirectional (yin-yang) Doppler flow pattern of the pseudoaneurysm. The pseudoaneurysm was eventually treated with thrombin injection.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.250117&amp;id=fig2">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div></section><section id="bibliography" role="doc-bibliography"><h2>Suggested Readings</h2><div role="list"><div role="listitem"><div id="r1" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">American College of Radiology Practice Parameter for the Performance of Stereotactic/Tomosynthesis-guided Breast Interventional Procedures. <a href="https://gravitas.acr.org/PPTS/GetDocumentView?docId=65+&amp;releaseId=2">https://gravitas.acr.org/PPTS/GetDocumentView?docId=65+&amp;releaseId=2</a>. Updated October 1, 2024. Accessed October 24, 2024.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=American+College+of+Radiology+Practice+Parameter+for+the+Performance+of+Stereotactic%2FTomosynthesis-guided+Breast+Interventional+Procedures">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem"><div id="r2" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Chetlen AL, Kasales C, Mack J, Schetter S, Zhu J. Hematoma Formation During Breast Core Needle Biopsy in Women Taking Antithrombotic Therapy. <em>AJR Am J Roentgenol</em> 2013;201(1):215–222.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.2214/AJR.12.9930">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/23789678/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Hematoma+Formation+During+Breast+Core+Needle+Biopsy+in+Women+Taking+Antithrombotic+Therapy&amp;author=AL+Chetlen&amp;author=C+Kasales&amp;author=J+Mack&amp;author=S+Schetter&amp;author=J+Zhu&amp;publication_year=2013&amp;journal=AJR+Am+J+Roentgenol&amp;pages=215-222&amp;doi=10.2214%2FAJR.12.9930&amp;pmid=23789678">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem"><div id="r3" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Goudreau S, Grimm LJ, Srinivasan A, et al. Bleeding Complications After Breast Core-needle Biopsy: An Approach to Managing Patients on Antithrombotic Therapy. <em>J Breast Imaging</em> 2022;4(3):241–252.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1093/jbi/wbac020">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/38416973/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Bleeding+Complications+After+Breast+Core-needle+Biopsy%3A+An+Approach+to+Managing+Patients+on+Antithrombotic+Therapy&amp;author=S+Goudreau&amp;author=LJ+Grimm&amp;author=A+Srinivasan&amp;publication_year=2022&amp;journal=J+Breast+Imaging&amp;pages=241-252&amp;doi=10.1093%2Fjbi%2Fwbac020&amp;pmid=38416973">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem"><div id="r4" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Lewis JD, Groszkiewicz A, Hefelfinger L, et al. Clinically significant bleeding complications of percutaneous breast biopsy: 10-year analysis and a proposed management algorithm. <em>Clin Imaging</em> 2023;104:110017.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.clinimag.2023.110017">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37979400/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Clinically+significant+bleeding+complications+of+percutaneous+breast+biopsy%3A+10-year+analysis+and+a+proposed+management+algorithm&amp;author=JD+Lewis&amp;author=A+Groszkiewicz&amp;author=L+Hefelfinger&amp;publication_year=2023&amp;journal=Clin+Imaging&amp;pages=110017&amp;doi=10.1016%2Fj.clinimag.2023.110017&amp;pmid=37979400">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem"><div id="r5" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Loving VA, Johnston BS, Reddy DH, et al. Antithrombotic Therapy and Hematoma Risk during Image-guided Core-Needle Breast Biopsy. <em>Radiology</em> 2023;306(1):79–86.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1148/radiol.220548">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35997610/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Antithrombotic+Therapy+and+Hematoma+Risk+during+Image-guided+Core-Needle+Breast+Biopsy&amp;author=VA+Loving&amp;author=BS+Johnston&amp;author=DH+Reddy&amp;publication_year=2023&amp;journal=Radiology&amp;pages=79-86&amp;doi=10.1148%2Fradiol.220548&amp;pmid=35997610">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem"><div id="r6" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">McMahon P, Reichman M, Dodelzon K. Bleeding risk after percutaneous breast needle biopsy in patients on anticoagulation therapy. <em>Clin Imaging</em> 2021;70:114–117.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.clinimag.2020.09.014">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33157367/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Bleeding+risk+after+percutaneous+breast+needle+biopsy+in+patients+on+anticoagulation+therapy&amp;author=P+McMahon&amp;author=M+Reichman&amp;author=K+Dodelzon&amp;publication_year=2021&amp;journal=Clin+Imaging&amp;pages=114-117&amp;doi=10.1016%2Fj.clinimag.2020.09.014&amp;pmid=33157367">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem"><div id="r7" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">O’Donnell JS, Lavin M. Perioperative management of patients with von Willebrand disease. <em>Hematology</em> 2019;2019(1):604–609.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1182/hematology.2019000065">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31808837/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Perioperative+management+of+patients+with+von+Willebrand+disease&amp;author=JS+O%E2%80%99Donnell&amp;author=M+Lavin&amp;publication_year=2019&amp;journal=Hematology&amp;pages=604-609&amp;doi=10.1182%2Fhematology.2019000065&amp;pmid=31808837">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem"><div id="r8" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Patel IJ, Rahim S, Davidson JC, et al. Society of Interventional Radiology Consensus Guidelines for the Periprocedural Management of Thrombotic and Bleeding Risk in Patients Undergoing Percutaneous Image-Guided Interventions-Part II: Recommendations: Endorsed by the Canadian Association for Interventional Radiology and the Cardiovascular and Interventional Radiological Society of Europe. <em>J Vasc Interv Radiol</em> 2019;30(8):1168–1184.e1.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jvir.2019.04.017">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31229333/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Society+of+Interventional+Radiology+Consensus+Guidelines+for+the+Periprocedural+Management+of+Thrombotic+and+Bleeding+Risk+in+Patients+Undergoing+Percutaneous+Image-Guided+Interventions-Part+II%3A+Recommendations%3A+Endorsed+by+the+Canadian+Association+for+Interventional+Radiology+and+the+Cardiovascular+and+Interventional+Radiological+Society+of+Europe&amp;author=IJ+Patel&amp;author=S+Rahim&amp;author=JC+Davidson&amp;publication_year=2019&amp;journal=J+Vasc+Interv+Radiol&amp;pages=1168-1184.e1&amp;doi=10.1016%2Fj.jvir.2019.04.017&amp;pmid=31229333">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem"><div id="r9" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Reichman MB, McMahon P, Dwyer M, et al. Bleeding Events After Image-Guided Breast Biopsies: Comparison of Patients Temporarily Discontinuing Versus Maintaining Antithrombotic Therapy During Biopsy. <em>AJR Am J Roentgenol</em> 2023;221(4):438–449.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.2214/AJR.23.29164">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37162038/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Bleeding+Events+After+Image-Guided+Breast+Biopsies%3A+Comparison+of+Patients+Temporarily+Discontinuing+Versus+Maintaining+Antithrombotic+Therapy+During+Biopsy&amp;author=MB+Reichman&amp;author=P+McMahon&amp;author=M+Dwyer&amp;publication_year=2023&amp;journal=AJR+Am+J+Roentgenol&amp;pages=438-449&amp;doi=10.2214%2FAJR.23.29164&amp;pmid=37162038">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem"><div id="r10" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Somerville P, Seifert PJ, Destounis SV, Murphy PF, Young W. Anticoagulation and Bleeding Risk After Core Needle Biopsy. <em>AJR Am J Roentgenol</em> 2008;191(4):1194–1197.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.2214/AJR.07.3537">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/18806164/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Anticoagulation+and+Bleeding+Risk+After+Core+Needle+Biopsy&amp;author=P+Somerville&amp;author=PJ+Seifert&amp;author=SV+Destounis&amp;author=PF+Murphy&amp;author=W+Young&amp;publication_year=2008&amp;journal=AJR+Am+J+Roentgenol&amp;pages=1194-1197&amp;doi=10.2214%2FAJR.07.3537&amp;pmid=18806164">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div></div></section></div></section></div><div class="core-collateral" role="dialog" aria-modal="true"><div id="core-collateral-info" data-active-pane="false"><header><h2><i class="icon-info" aria-hidden="true"></i>Information &amp; Authors</h2><